build.md
     1→# The build command
     3→The build command is used to render your book:
     4→
     5→```bash
     6→mdbook build
     7→```
     8→
     9→It will try to parse your `SUMMARY.md` file to understand the structure of your
    10→book and fetch the corresponding files. Note that this will also create files
    11→mentioned in `SUMMARY.md` which are not yet present.
    12→
    13→The rendered output will maintain the same directory structure as the source for
    14→convenience. Large books will therefore remain structured when rendered.
